title: Australia not asked to boost numbers against ISIS, Bishop says
text:
Australia not asked to boost numbers against ISIS, Bishop says By 9NEWS 
Australia has not been asked to increase its contribution to the battle against the Islamic State group, Foreign Minister Julie Bishop said. 
Ms Bishop said her meeting with US Vice President Mike Pence, the first high-level personal contact between Australia and the US since Donald Trump became president, was “warm and constructive”. 
Attention had been largely focused on the meeting due to the now-infamous first phone call between Mr Trump and Prime Minister Malcolm Turnbull earlier this year, which Mr Trump described as his “worst” call with any world leader. 
"There is a [30-day] review in the United States under way as to the strategy for defeating ISIS and I gave some input into the Vice President's thinking," she told reporters in Washington after the meeting. 
“This affects Australia and our security, the number of foreign terrorist fighters leaving Iraq and Syria as more gains are made is a concern.” 
She said foreign fighters leaving Iraq and Syria were a concern for both the US and Australia. 
We have to look at post-defeat of ISIS environments and scenarios," the minister said. 
Ms Bishop said the fact that the meeting went longer than scheduled was "a good sign" of strong relations with the Trump administration, playing down doubts which surfaced after the call between the two nations’ leaders. 
On Afghanistan, Ms Bishop said Australia's current military contribution was considered "appropriate". 
“We have not been asked to increase our contribution, our contribution is appropriate,” she said. 
She expected there would be opportunities this year for Mr Turnbull to meet face-to-face with Mr Trump, but would not go into details. 
She was hopeful Mr Pence would visit Australia during an expected tour of the Asia-Pacific region by the vice president. Ms Bishop said she also understood the US wanted to have a "constructive" relationship with China. © Nine Digital Pty Ltd 2017
